T*
(Section 1: STAR and BEI evidence collection) Tj
T*
(A structured interview should collect Situation, Task, Action and Result evidence.) Tj
T*
(If a candidate only says the team finished a project, ask about personal contribution.) Tj
T*
(If a candidate only says the result was good, ask about metrics, feedback and attribution.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Section 2: Pressure attribution probe) Tj
T*
(Pressure questions should challenge evidence quality, not attack the candidate.) Tj
T*
(Ask whether the result would still happen without the candidate's action.) Tj
T*
(Ask whether other factors could explain the metric change.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Section 3: Technical deep dive) Tj
T*
(Technical interviews should inspect constraints, tradeoffs, validation and failure handling.) Tj
T*
(Do not only ask terminology questions. Anchor the probe in a real project decision.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Section 4: Business case) Tj
T*
